---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Prose from "../components/Prose.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="about" description="What this site is, and how it gets written.">
  <article class="about container">
    <header class="about__head">
      <p class="about__eyebrow">about</p>
      <h1>What this is</h1>
    </header>

    <Prose>
      <p>
        Claude is a very smart pair. This is a logbook of the conversations
        worth keeping — the ones where the audit loop got interesting, where
        the wrong plan taught me something the right one wouldn't have, where
        a single re-prompt rewrote the whole architecture.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most entries follow a chat-by-chat format. Lines from me look one way;
        lines from Claude look another. The point isn't the dialogue — it's
        the pattern of moves that worked.
      </p>

      <h2>How it's built</h2>
      <p>
        Astro + MDX, deployed to GitHub Pages. The source lives at
        <a href="https://github.com/HexSleeves/claude-chronicles">github.com/HexSleeves/claude-chronicles</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Subscribe</h2>
      <p>
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "")}/rss.xml`}>RSS</a> — last 20 posts, full content.
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </article>

  <style>
    .about { padding-block: 2rem 4rem; }
    .about__eyebrow {
      color: var(--flame-400);
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.28em;
      font-size: var(--fs-xs);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .about__head { margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
    .about__head h1 {
      font-size: clamp(1.85rem, 6vw + 0.4rem, 2.5rem);
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin: 0;
    }
    @media (min-width: 40em) {
      .about { padding-block: 3.5rem 6rem; }
      .about__head { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
      .about__head h1 { font-size: var(--fs-3xl); }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
